  <%# --- Technological Leap Section --- %>
  <section class="py-20 bg-neutral-900">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row-reverse items-center gap-16">
        <%# Content %>
        <div class="w-full lg:w-1/2">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
            <div
              class="
                w-12 h-12 rounded-2xl bg-secondary flex items-center
                justify-center text-black font-bold text-xl shadow-lg
                shadow-secondary/20
              "
            >
              B
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white">
              The Technological Leap: 2D to 3D Fidelity
            </h2>
          </div>

          <p class="text-lg text-neutral-300 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
            Hadaa employs a specialized pipeline to ensure the resulting 3D
            visualization is accurate, preserved, and fully editable.
          </p>

          <div class="space-y-6">
            <%# Feature Item %>
            <div
              class="
                group p-5 rounded-2xl bg-neutral-800/30 border
                border-white/5 hover:border-secondary/30 transition-colors
              "
            >
              <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-secondary"></span>
                The Clay Rendering Pipeline
              </h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 pl-4 border-l border-white/10 ml-1">
                When an upload is made, our system automatically detects the
                sketch and routes it to a specialized pipeline where the drawing
                is first transformed into a 3D clay rendering.
              </p>
            </div>

            <%# Feature Item %>
            <div
              class="
                group p-5 rounded-2xl bg-neutral-800/30 border
                border-white/5 hover:border-secondary/30 transition-colors
              "
            >
              <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-accent"></span>
                Photorealistic Finalization
              </h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 pl-4 border-l border-white/10 ml-1">
                This clay rendering is then updated into a photorealistic photo
                of the scene, always preserving the scene's original layout and
                angles established in the sketch.
              </p>
            </div>

            <%# Feature Item %>
            <div
              class="
                group p-5 rounded-2xl bg-neutral-800/30 border
                border-white/5 hover:border-secondary/30 transition-colors
              "
            >
              <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-white"></span>
                Handling Unspecified Elements
              </h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 pl-4 border-l border-white/10 ml-1">
                Elements not specified in the sketch (like exact materials,
                textures, or plant species) are added immediately after the
                photorealistic version is created using the Intelligent AI
                Prompt Editor. You are always in control of the final aesthetic.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <%# Visual %>
        <div class="w-full lg:w-1/2">
          <div
            class="
              relative rounded-3xl overflow-hidden border border-white/10
              shadow-2xl bg-neutral-900
            "
